This toggleable item allows you to encounter extra
{pageend:<color=#F01E1EFF>Regional Pokemon</color>!}
{pageend:Choosing a flower is for Luminescent 3.0 when all}
{pageend:previous regions will be available in the wild.}
{pageend:In the current build, all flowers lead to the same}
{pageend:encounters. "Regional" Pokémon include anything}
{pageend:up to gen 4 that has regionals, or regional}
{pageend:evolutions (Braviary is not in gen 4, so there is no}
{pageend:Braviary or Hisuian Braviary).}
{pageend:More information can be found on}
https://luminescent.team/.

{pageend:The <color=#F01E1EFF>Move Reminder</color> is now in your party menu!}
It only appears if the Pokémon has five or more
{pageend:moves in its memory, and includes TMs you own.}
(Wonder what the <color=#F01E1EFF>old Reminder</color> is doing now,
then?)

{pageend:The <color=#F01E1EFF>Move Reminder</color> is now in your party menu!}
It only appears if the Pokémon can know more
than four moves, and the selection includes any
{pageend:TMs in your inventory.}
Deleting moves entirely must still be done in
{pageend:Canalave City.}
(If the Move Reminder is here... wonder what the
<color=#F01E1EFF>old Reminder's</color> up to?)

You can change your Pokémon’s <color=#F01E1EFF>Nickname</color> at any
{pageend:time from the party menu!}
{pageend:If the option is not there, you may have a bad}
install.

